'''Mountain trolls''' are [[aggressive]] creatures which can be found patrolling various mountainous areas.

They are commonly killed as part of an assigned [[Slayer task]] of "[[Trolls]]".

Trolls regenerate health quickly but are still vulnerable to [[poison]]. They usually use [[crush weapons]], which, combined with their relatively high Strength, can hit rather hard. However, they attack slowly and are quite inaccurate, so it's not strictly necessary to use [[protection prayers]] for players that have high [[Defence]]. A good strategy for conserving supplies is to use [[Bones to Peaches]] on the Big bones that they drop; this will almost always cover any damage they manage to deal. Bringing a [[Staff of fire|Staff of Fire]] (or similar item) and [[Nature rune|Nature runes]] is recommended in order to [[alchemy|alchemise]] their frequent low-level armour and weapon drops.

On [[Death Plateau (location)|Death Plateau]], they can be [[safespot]]ted from many areas; all of the stone fences and pretty much every other obstacle in the area can be shot over with ranged or magic. [[Stick]] and [[Rock (Troll)|Rock]] count as mountain trolls and can easily be safespotted using the stone fence on the west side of the plateau for additional [[Slayer]] XP (beware that these two hit much harder and more often than standard mountain trolls). Alternatively, they can be safespotted around the corners of some rock piles in the [[Keldagrim]] entrance area.

